Use of the OpenAI API
We use the services of OpenAI, including the OpenAI API, for various purposes within our Hundeo app to improve interactions and personalized recommendations. The OpenAI API enables us to respond to user requests with automated but precisely tailored responses, optimize interaction experiences and continuously improve the usability of our app.
Processed data
By using the OpenAI API, personal data may be processed and temporarily stored insofar as this is necessary to respond to user queries or to provide personalized content. This includes, in particular, text entries or other information that users enter or provide within the app. OpenAI also processes usage data and metadata for security purposes and to optimize its service.
Purposes and legal bases of processing
The OpenAI API is used for the purpose of improving our app services and optimizing the user experience. If we ask for consent to use the OpenAI API, the legal basis for processing is consent. Otherwise, processing is based on our legitimate interest in efficient, interactive and user-friendly app services.
Notes on legal bases
The processing of data in the context of the OpenAI API is based on consent (Art. 6 para. 1 sentence 1 lit. a GDPR), in the context of the provision of our contractual services (Art. 6 para. 1 sentence 1 lit. b GDPR) or on the basis of our legitimate interests in the improvement and personalization of our services (Art. 6 para. 1 sentence 1 lit. f GDPR).
Services used and service providers:
